"{\"uid\": \"mbr.co.uk-news-racing-news-rubbings-racing-says-tom-pidcock-about-controversial-move-in-olympic-mountain-bike-xco-race-that-clinched-gold-440316\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Britain's Tom Pidcock explains late race move and coming together with Silver medallist Viktor Koretzky, saying \\\"I had to go for a gap\\\".\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.5700590876821817, \"rank\": 0.7540333816935532, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boos greetedTom Pidcock as he crossed the line in front of a partisan French crowd to claim the gold medal in the Mountain Bike Cross-Country raceat the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 208, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6792484407059587, \"rank\": 0.3875422049889685, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 297, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reaction came after Pidcock got his elbows out and squeezed past home favourite Viktor Koretzky with less than 1km to go before the finish line in a race led mostly by the Frenchman.\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ELANCOURT, FRANCE - JULY 29: Thomas Pidcock of Team Great Britain celebrates at finish line as gold medal winner during the Men's Cross-Country on day three of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 at Elancourt Hill on July 29, 2024 in Elancourt, France.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ELANCOURT\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}, {\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 547, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9080913044533124, \"rank\": 0.10121085302311288, \"text\": \"Team Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9725613440037943, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elancourt\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}, {\"begin\": 738, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9201114383552589, \"rank\": 0.04437340926820128, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by Tim de Waele/Getty Images)  \\\"I am keeping my glasses on for a reason,\\\" an emotional Pidcock told the BBC after crossing the line to take gold.\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 769, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999990006966063, \"rank\": 3.3071965422883913e-07, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999094915019714, \"rank\": 9.042821967309285e-05, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics is so special.\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You never give up, you give everything, and that's what I had to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock suffered anearly front puncture, and slightly botched wheel change,that looked set to end his chances.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thinks were going so well my mechanic was not ready,\\\" Pidcock said.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But he did a super fast change in the end, my bike was perfect apart from the puncture.\\\"\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He put in a super human effort to regain the lead, before attacking almost immediately in an effort to drop Koretzky and South African Alan Hatherley.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Koretzky stuck to his wheel like glue, and launched his own savage attack at the top of the final climb, to open up a 20m gap on the Brit.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A bobble off camera brought the two riders back together on the final run-in to the finish, and Pidcock, seeing a split line around a tree, dived to the inside and accelerated, getting his wheel ahead of Koretzky before the tracks converged, and forcing the French rider to brake and unclip.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6792484407059587, \"rank\": 0.3875422049889685, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was enough to create a gap and earn Pidcock his second Olympic XCO Gold medal.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a post-race interview to Adam Blythe of Discovery Plus/Eurosport, Tom Pidcock was unapologetic about his last lap move; \\\"Rubbing's racing!\\\"\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Blythe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\"}, {\"begin\": 2009, \"end\": 2020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"the young star said, quoting Days of Thunder (the NASCAR film with Tom Cruise).\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2133, \"end\": 2139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR\", \"score\": 0.9999777011376993, \"rank\": 2.2293828916173072e-05, \"text\": \"NASCAR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR\"}, {\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could not get rid of Viktor.\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew how fast he is on the last lap.\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end I just had to go for a gap.\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's what I have always done and the Olympics no different.\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sorry for him, his the support was amazing, but it's the Olympics, you have got to go all-in.\\\"\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock told the BBC: \\\"That's racing, some people might view it differently\\u2026 but that's what sport is, not giving up.\\\"\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2451, \"end\": 2454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999094915019714, \"rank\": 9.042821967309285e-05, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}]}]}"